SIMPLE: stuttering
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stuttering
<hw>Stut"ter*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of one who stutters;
-- restricted by some physiologists to defective speech due to inability
to form the proper sounds, the breathing being normal, as distinguished
from <xex>stammering</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stuttering</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stuttering
<hw>Stut"ter*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Apt to stutter; hesitating;
stammering.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Stut"ter*ing*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sty</ent>⟦br⟧
